RT_RANDOM_NUMBER_HERE&amp;n=a621feb9\" /></a>\n    \n    <img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/ucllc/fpo/~4/Ln7MJWIjpbk\" />',1,'2012-05-25 05:50:00','kelly'),(341,2,'a6f198884d23309167039448951c9efe','http://bits.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/05/23/todays-scuttlebot-cyberspy-school-and-internet-destruction/','2012-05-25 21:58:01','Today\'s Scuttlebot: Cyberspy School and Internet Destruction','http://bits.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/05/23/todays-scuttlebot-cyberspy-school-and-internet-destruction/','','The technology reporters and editors of The New York Times scour the Web for important and peculiar items. Wednesday\'s selection includes I.B.M. banning Apple\'s Siri because it doesn\'t trust her, a missing iPhone posting photo clues on the Web and a venture capitalist saying there is little sexism in his industry.',1,'2012-05-23 18:17:04','By THE NEW YORK TIMES'),(342,2,'616a4c8dfc3e72b82e3e798fa186b775','http://bits.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/05/23/google-cleared-of-java-patent-violation/','2012-05-25 21:58:01','Google Cleared of Infringing on Oracle\'s Java Patents','http://bits.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/05/23/google-cleared-of-java-patent-violation/','','Jurors in Oracle\'s lawsuit against Google have found that the search giant violated no patents on the Java programming language when it created the Android operating system. Barring any surprising last-minute judgements, a case that once held the prospect of shaking up the smartphone business will very likely end quietly.',1,'2012-05-23 13:57:51','By QUENTIN HARDY'),(343,7,'5c41c894f8ab69356b6afbc36c7bb50a','tag:www.underconsideration.com,2012:/fpo//1.922','2012-05-25 21:58:01','Portland General Store Brochure','http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/ucllc/fpo/~3/mEOcFrHW1KI/portland-general-store-brochure.php','','\n        <img src=\"http://www.underconsideration.com/fpo/project_images/portland_general_00.jpg\" alt=\"Lead Image\" />\n        \n        \n        Designed by <a href=\"http://stitchdesignco.com\">Stitch Design Co.</a